### Issue #18: feat: R32 resolution + single-elimination knockout sim with extra-time/penalties (simulation/knockout.py)

## Goal
Turn final group standings into the 16 concrete Round-of-32 ties via the WC2026 bracket template, then simulate the single-elimination tree (R32 → R16 → QF → SF → Final) where each tie is resolved by a sampled scoreline, with draws decided by extra-time (`λ × extra_time_factor`) then a penalty coin-flip.

## Context
`data/wc2026_bracket.py` encodes the slotting rules: `R32_SLOTS` (`wc2026_bracket.py:41-58`) is 16 `(home_slot, away_slot)` pairs using slot codes like `"1A"` (group A winner), `"2A"` (runner-up), `"3ABCDF"` (best-third placeholder). `resolve_r32(standings)`... [truncated, 14813 bytes omitted]

